title: Brittney Griner Has Begun Serving Nine-Year Sentence at a Russian Penal Colony
description: The development dashed hopes that the American basketball star was being moved with an eye to imminently being freed.

title: Italian Catholic Bishops Release First Sex-Abuse Report
description: The national study of clerical sex abuse marks a limited and belated move in a country where the church enjoys significant social and cultural clout.

title: Biden Pushes Back on Kyiv's Claims Russia Shot Missile That Hit Poland
description: Top NATO officials say the missile was likely a Soviet-made weapon fired by a Ukrainian air-defense system, adding there’s no evidence it was aimed at Poland.

title: Kamala Harris Leads U.S. Push to Bolster Economic Ties in Asia
description: The Biden administration is pursuing closer business ties and higher environmental and labor standards at an APEC summit in Bangkok.

title: Developing Nations Seek Faster Emission Cuts From Rich World at COP27
description: Developing countries are pushing wealthy ones to accelerate sharply their plans to cut greenhouse-gas emissions over the next decade, a new salvo in negotiations at the COP27 climate summit.

title: Iran Rebuked by U.N. Over Stonewalling of Its Nuclear Investigation
description: The probe has become a key obstacle for the U.S. and Iran to revive their nuclear deal.

title: Japan's Leader Seeks Steady China Ties in First Meeting With Xi
description: Military tensions between the two countries have risen as Tokyo worries about being drawn into a conflict over Taiwan.

title: Resurrection of U.S.-China Ties Boosts COP27 Climate Talks
description: Official cooperation, frozen after Nancy Pelosi’s visit to Taiwan, has been revived for the global climate gathering after Biden and Xi met in Bali, Indonesia.

title: Three Found Guilty of Downing MH17 Over Ukraine
description: A panel of Dutch judges found three men guilty over the shooting down of a passenger jet over eastern Ukraine in 2014.

title: U.K. Unveils Tax Increases and Spending Cuts to Shore Up Finances
description: Treasury chief Jeremy Hunt laid out his spending plans for Britain amid high inflation, rising interest rates

title: Egypt Dims the Lights to Free Up More Gas for Europe
description: The country is cutting back on its domestic energy use so it can sell more gas and help tackle its economic crisis.

title: Russia Launches Fresh Missile Strikes on Ukraine
description: A barrage of missiles targeting the capital Kyiv and other cities killed at least eight people, days after the Kremlin’s military carried out some of the heaviest bombing of the war.

title: Russia Agrees to Renew Ukraine Grain Deal, U.N. Says
description: Moscow has agreed to renew the deal that allows Ukrainian agricultural products to be exported through the Black Sea region, U.N. Secretary-General António Guterres said.

title: Former U.K. Ambassador Among Thousands to Be Freed From Myanmar Prison
description: The amnesty is unlikely to improve Myanmar’s relations with the West, which frayed after a military coup derailed the country’s transition to democracy.

title: North Korea Fires Ballistic Missile After U.S. Summit With South Korea, Japan
description: The short-range missile fired off the North’s east coast before landing in waters between peninsula and Japan.
